Magnificent work from Bifidus-sensei. After re-read, i suppose the guy choose to move in with those to in countryside.

For those who don't understand the ending: being the guy he is, having been horribly miserable and stressed for so long and suddenly, almost magically finding dreamlike happiness in the middle of nowhere, and seeing people he sees every day in the streets of this middle of nowhere town sometimes just disappear (most likely moving elsewhere or passing away), he basically sometimes worried if this was all a dream or an illusion and all this happiness would just disappear on him one day. Luckily his ladies managed to dispel those worries and ground him in reality again.

@Zerobero1235 No it's not an illusion. Our Main Character is feeling need for human interaction, something real. Because he had a hard time at his previous company. So when he had vacations, he decided to spend them in the countryside. However there were not much life over there either. Until the woman and her daughter brings him to their home. At the end when he go pick up some ice cream, the streets are desert, no social interaction anywhere around, and it makes him feel anxious, like his life is just an illusion. But when he comes back at home, his relationship with the two women, their social interactions etc help him overcome this anxiety and the sad town he's living in. That everything is not an illusion.
